reinhard von hanxleden's home page



reinhard von hanxleden




reinhard v. hanxleden received his vordiplom in computer
science/physics from christian albrechts university in kiel, germany,
in 1987 and his m.s. in computer science from pennsylvania state
university in 1989.  in 1995, he received his ph.d. in computer
science from rice university.  since january 1995 he is a research
associate at daimler benz ag in berlin.  his research interests
include data parallel compilers for irregular problems,
hardware/software codesign, and high performance hubcaps.

for contact info, finger reinhard&lt;at&gt;cs.rice.edu.
[in his quest for cutting down electronic junk mail, reinhard v. hanxleden hopes that whatever search engine is crawling the domain for email addresses for whatever purpose is dumb enough to just look for strings containing @-signs.]


dissertation: compiler support for machine-independent parallelization of irregular problems

